Raymond McKee https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raymond_McKee 0 Raymond McKee born Eldon Raymond McKee (December 7, 1892 – October 3, 1984) was an American actor. He appeared in 173 films between 1912 and 1935. His film debut was in The Lovers' Signal (1912). During the production of The Unbeliever in 1918, McKee worked with his future wife, Marguerite Courtot. They worked again in the 1922 Down to the Sea in Ships. They married after the production of the film and were wed for 60 years until his death in 1984.
